This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the problem of building a classification model using data partitioning and ensemble methods. It also involves the use of Gini impurity approach for finding the best split percentage of noise filter ratio, which is a common technique in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.DM (Data Mining) as data partitioning, bagging, and boosting are commonly used techniques in this field. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category as the paper deals with improving the performance of classification models, which is a common problem in AI. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a possible sub-category as ensemble methods are commonly used in image classification tasks. 

Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as ensemble methods are also used in neural network models.
